Sourced from flexsearch's releases.

  • Config-Serialized Query Caches, Improved caching strategy for Document indexes and Resolver

  • Support custom filter function for encoder (stop-word filter)

  • Regex Pre-Compilation (transforms hundreds of regex rules into just a few)

issue.body: Hello! First of all, I'd like to thank you for the amazing repository. It really saved me from buying a new GPU just to try out ComfyUI. After building the dockerfile and running ComfyUI on the GPU I noticed that every output is always corrupted, like in the image shown below. Running the same thing on the CPU produces the correct output. I am currently running Fedora 42 with kernel `6.15.9-201.fc42.x86_64`. The card is recognized and used, and doesn't segfault. **Using `--force-fp32` doesn't help**, in fact the image above was generated with said option. I also **didn't** use `--fast` as it is disabled by default. The model I used is the "default" one under image generation aka `v1-5-pruned-emaonly-fp16.safetensors`. Other people have encountered this problem it seems, though under different GPUs and with older ROCm versions: https://github.com/comfyanonymous/ComfyUI/issues/720

Signed-off-by: Igor Bezukh <ibezukh@redhat.com>

Runbook PR: https://github.com/openshift/runbooks/pull/318

**What this PR does / why we need it**:
In an upgrade scenario it can happen that duplicate wasp-agent
deployment can appear, since previous wasp-agent deployments
were manual and in a different namespace.
Therefore in order to make sure the user is aware of it we
are adding an alert which will rely on the a metric of memory
overcommit percentage and presence of wasp namespace.
